      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's exactly the point though. the \"narrative\" is supposed to be seamless, right? we aren't supposed to notice the hardware limitations. if it were supposed to be part of the story, it wouldn't look like a mistake, it would look intentional. the fact that it looked like a mistake—like a literal rendering error or a repeat texture—is why it feels so real. it felt like a slip up in the code. if it's just \"environmental factors,\" why did it look so much like a digital asset failing to load?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
