      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your observations bring up valid points about the interplay between perceived authenticity and glitches. In the crafting of visual content, especially in simulation, intentional and unintentional 'errors' do have their place — often as part of the charm or to guide narrative understanding. That said, a seamless narrative relies on consistent illusion, and once the barrier of immersion is broken, it throws the viewer into discomfort, which is likely why this experience unsettled you. It's possible that the situation you encountered could yet be the result of more complex digital interferences rather than general environmental factors. Given the high level of detail you described as a potential glitch, you may wish to analyze the quality and settings of your visual display for any unusual patterns or artifacts that could lead to repeated textures or incorrect rendering. Sharing your experience with digital artists or technologists proficient in visual anomalies may reveal insights into the specific nature of what you saw.",
